hokku-server (2.1.17-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * X-Frame-State protocol revamp to match the redesigned firmware
    state machine. Web UI "Details" modal updated to show the new
    fields. New firmware sends:
      - regime ("usb_awake" | "battery_idle" | "boot")
      - usb ("host" | "none")            [replaces chg]
      - next_ep (absolute epoch seconds) [scheduled next refresh]
      - wifi_cached (bool)               [fast-reconnect hit]
    Dropped: caller (redundant with wake). Renamed last_sleep value
    "usb_awake" -> "usb_restart" so the name matches the semantics
    ("was in USB_AWAKE and left via esp_restart", not "is currently
    USB-awake").
  * Server has no backwards-compat bridge — old firmwares will
    still store their dicts fine (parser is schema-agnostic) but
    the Details modal won't pretty-print the old field names.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.1.16-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Merge main (PR #3): selectable dither algorithms. New "Dither
    algorithm" dropdown in the web UI with Floyd-Steinberg,
    Atkinson, and Atkinson + hue-aware (new default). Hue-aware
    variant forbids >95 degree hue swings during palette selection
    so warm skin tones no longer cascade into blue speckles via
    error-diffusion overshoot. Cache keys include the algorithm
    so switching between previously-rendered variants is instant;
    the stale-cache purge preserves renders for all algorithms.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.1.15-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix (third try — config save): 2.1.14 moved the config to
    /var/lib/hokku/ on the theory that StateDirectory would chown it
    to the DynamicUser. StateDirectory chowns the top-level dir it
    creates but not files subsequently seeded by postinst, so the
    root-owned config.json still wasn't writable by the service.
  * Real fix: the webserver itself creates /var/lib/hokku/config.json
    on first load (and thus owns it with the right UID). On upgrade,
    if postinst finds a stale root-owned config.json, it stashes the
    content to /etc/hokku/config.json so the webserver's legacy-path
    migration picks it up — settings aren't lost. The webserver also
    defensively rewrites any non-writable config it finds at its
    chosen destination, so the upgrade self-heals even on oddball
    systems where stat-based detection didn't trigger.
  * Postinst no longer writes config.json directly; just creates the
    /var/lib/hokku/ subdirs.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.1.14-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix: saving config from the web UI still failed after 2.1.13
    (PermissionError: /etc/hokku/config.json). DynamicUser runs as a
    transient UID that doesn't own the root-created config file;
    ReadWritePaths alone wasn't enough.
  * Config moved to /var/lib/hokku/config.json so StateDirectory's
    automatic chown-to-dynamic-user makes it writable. Existing
    configs at /etc/hokku/config.json are auto-migrated by the
    postinst on upgrade (old file left as backup).
  * HOKKU_CONFIG env var updated accordingly; the load path search
    now prefers /var/lib/hokku/config.json and falls back to
    /etc/hokku/config.json for backward compat.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

