hokku-server (2.1.11-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * X-Frame-State header replaces X-Battery-mV: firmware sends a single
    JSON object per request (fw, boot, wake, caller, uptime_s, bat_mv,
    chg, last_sleep, rssi, heap_kb, spurious, cfg_ver, clk_now,
    sleep_err_s); server stores the whole dict.
  * Web UI: Connected Screens table adds Battery column and per-row
    Details button (modal shows the full device-state dict formatted).
  * Overdue-screen warning: yellow banner + row shading when a screen
    is >1h past its scheduled next_update_at.
  * Debug Screen mode: new config toggle that forces every response to
    X-Sleep-Seconds=180 for fast image iteration; red banner while on.
  * Removed the "Server address" row from the config section.
  * Clock-drift measurement: firmware sets its system clock from
    X-Server-Time-Epoch on every response; server compares returned
    clk_now to its own time() for direct RTC drift measurement.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

